Can they... can they just follow
you for as long as they want?

534
00:32:53.223 --> 00:32:55.600
Well. that's a loaded question.

535
00:32:57.102 --> 00:32:59.521
What're you getting at?
Are you being followed?

536
00:32:59.604 --> 00:33:00.939
Uh...

537
00:33:01.022 --> 00:33:02.316
for about a week now.

538
00:33:02.399 --> 00:33:03.608
-A week?
-Yeah.

539
00:33:07.404 --> 00:33:09.197
They think I saw
this kid right before

540
00:33:09.280 --> 00:33:11.033
he upped and disappeared.

541
00:33:11.116 --> 00:33:12.367
Did you? John: No.

542
00:33:12.450 --> 00:33:14.036
And I've offered
everything that I can.

543
00:33:14.119 --> 00:33:15.912
Time.
conversation. theories.

544
00:33:15.995 --> 00:33:17.456
I mean. I gave 'em
the keys to my house.

545
00:33:17.539 --> 00:33:19.374
Search it. I says.

546
00:33:19.457 --> 00:33:20.751
But. now. I've got...

547
00:33:20.834 --> 00:33:23.128
friends. employees.
and perfect strangers asking me

548
00:33:23.211 --> 00:33:25.213
all these questions 'cause
they're with me all the time.

549
00:33:25.296 --> 00:33:27.424
Okay. Who's this?

550
00:33:27.507 --> 00:33:29.259
It's Des Plaines PD.

551
00:33:29.342 --> 00:33:31.178
Allen Fanholm and Mike Albrecht.

552
00:33:31.261 --> 00:33:32.220
You know 'em?

553
00:33:32.303 --> 00:33:33.639
Yeah.

554
00:33:33.722 --> 00:33:35.557
Work with Joe Kozenczak.

555
00:33:35.640 --> 00:33:37.184
Yeah. And.

556
00:33:37.267 --> 00:33:39.144
and Detective Tovar.

557
00:33:39.227 --> 00:33:41.396
All right.
Well. let me. um...

558
00:33:41.479 --> 00:33:43.314
let me give him a call.

559
00:33:44.733 --> 00:33:46.568
Were you gonna bill me for this?

560
00:33:46.651 --> 00:33:49.988
Well. we'll see
what they say first.

561
00:33:54.409 --> 00:33:55.410
Joe.

562
00:33:55.994 --> 00:33:57.496
-Sam.
-Perfect timing.

563
00:33:57.579 --> 00:33:59.498
-Oh.
-Holy shit.

564
00:33:59.581 --> 00:34:01.249
Were you just waiting
in your car for me to get here?

565
00:34:01.332 --> 00:34:03.585
-Yeah.
-Let me guess.

566
00:34:03.668 --> 00:34:05.587
-You got your first client?
-Uh. nothing official.

567
00:34:05.670 --> 00:34:07.130
Just poking around.

568
00:34:07.213 --> 00:34:09.341
For an acquaintance.
-Yeah. Who is it?

569
00:34:09.424 --> 00:34:10.508
John Wayne Gacy.

570
00:34:13.178 --> 00:34:14.304
You've been following him
for a week now.

571
00:34:14.387 --> 00:34:15.264
He been cooperating?

572
00:34:15.347 --> 00:34:17.432
-Yup.
-Good.

573
00:34:17.515 --> 00:34:19.434
You gonna charge him?

574
00:34:19.517 --> 00:34:21.395
Haven't decided yet.

575
00:34:21.478 --> 00:34:25.148
Well. time to piss or get
off the pot. my friend.

576
00:34:25.231 --> 00:34:26.231
Or what?

577
00:34:27.067 --> 00:34:30.279
Advise him to file
a civil suit for harassment.

578
00:34:30.362 --> 00:34:32.239
Good luck with that.

579
00:34:32.322 --> 00:34:33.448
You're not gonna pull your men?

580
00:34:33.531 --> 00:34:34.531
No.

581
00:34:50.548 --> 00:34:53.468
There. There. He's right there.

582
00:34:53.551 --> 00:34:55.137
-That car?
-Yeah. Come on.

583
00:35:12.529 --> 00:35:14.072
Let's get in there.

584
00:35:15.365 --> 00:35:16.658
Private property. man.

585
00:35:16.741 --> 00:35:18.201
My ma's a member.

586
00:35:24.249 --> 00:35:26.084
Hey. Come on. Say hi to my ma.

587
00:35:35.135 --> 00:35:36.511
Hi. Ma.

588
00:35:36.594 --> 00:35:40.182
-Oh. Mike. What a surprise.
-Nice to see you.

589
00:35:40.265 --> 00:35:41.558
Hey. how are you? How are you?

590
00:35:41.641 --> 00:35:43.101
Alderman.

591
00:35:47.272 --> 00:35:48.607
I'll catch up with you in a bit.

592
00:35:48.690 --> 00:35:50.817
There's some troublemakers
I gotta take care of here.

593
00:35:52.444 --> 00:35:53.528
Well. well. well.

594
00:35:55.321 --> 00:35:57.199
They let anybody
in here these days. huh?

595
00:35:57.282 --> 00:35:59.534
John. this is my son. Mike.

596
00:35:59.617 --> 00:36:01.161
and his friend. Al.

597
00:36:02.454 --> 00:36:03.538
This is your son?

598
00:36:03.621 --> 00:36:05.415
Yeah.

599
00:36:05.498 --> 00:36:10.128
Wow. You made
a good-looking kid. Gladys.

600
00:36:10.211 --> 00:36:12.214
Oh.

601
00:36:12.297 --> 00:36:14.091
What a camera-face.

602
00:36:14.174 --> 00:36:15.425
You two know each other?

603
00:36:15.508 --> 00:36:16.677
Yeah.
These guys are my bodyguards.

604
00:36:18.887 --> 00:36:21.139
Say. you guys know
a good place to get some pie?

605
00:36:21.222 --> 00:36:22.641
I got a hankering for pie.

606
00:36:22.724 --> 00:36:24.726
Now. what kind of pie
do you want?

607
00:36:24.809 --> 00:36:27.354
Gladys. it's the holidays.
so it's gotta be pumpkin.

608
00:36:27.437 --> 00:36:29.564
-Or a pecan.
-Or a pecan.

609
00:36:29.647 --> 00:36:32.234
That is right. That's right.

610
00:36:32.317 --> 00:36:37.197
Pumpkin reminds me of my ma.
'cause she used to bake 'em

611
00:36:37.280 --> 00:36:38.657
right around this time of year.

612
00:36:38.740 --> 00:36:42.411
And. you know. my dad.
he'd come home from work...

613
00:36:42.494 --> 00:36:43.787
he was a mechanic.

614
00:36:43.870 --> 00:36:46.373
so he'd come home
stinking of sweat and gas.

615
00:36:46.456 --> 00:36:48.792
And he'd grab my mom
and give her a kiss

616
00:36:48.875 --> 00:36:50.419
and she'd say. "Gosh."

617
00:36:50.502 --> 00:36:52.879
Slide him away and say.
"Shower. you stink."

618
00:36:52.962 --> 00:36:56.800
And. you know. he'd. he'd
kiss us kids and he'd...

619
00:36:56.883 --> 00:37:01.221
he'd sniff the kitchen.
you know. smell the pie.

620
00:37:01.304 --> 00:37:04.766
And he'd say. "That's a mother's
love right there."

621
00:37:04.849 --> 00:37:06.226
Aww. for cute.

622
00:37:07.519 --> 00:37:08.895
So how long you've been
a member here. John?

623
00:37:08.978 --> 00:37:11.231
You know. I. I.
I never seen you here before.

624
00:37:11.314 --> 00:37:13.609
He's the most popular
non-member there is.

625
00:37:13.692 --> 00:37:15.485
Is that right?

626
00:37:15.568 --> 00:37:17.696
Yeah. I mean.
I get invites all the time.

627
00:37:17.779 --> 00:37:19.406
Yeah? John: Yeah.

628
00:37:19.489 --> 00:37:21.783
'Cause I got connections
with everybody

629
00:37:21.866 --> 00:37:23.827
from the mayor to the mob

630
00:37:23.910 --> 00:37:26.454
and all the muckety-mucks
in between.

631
00:37:29.332 --> 00:37:30.375
Um...

632
00:37:33.253 --> 00:37:37.758
word is that that Piest kid's
in Wisconsin. Hitchhiked.

633
00:37:37.841 --> 00:37:39.343
You got any idea where. John?

634
00:37:39.426 --> 00:37:40.844
I mean.
Wisconsin's a pretty big place.

635
00:37:40.927 --> 00:37:43.472
Oh. that I know.
'cause I got property up there.

636
00:37:43.555 --> 00:37:47.434
Yeah. Nevada. Minnesota.
Florida too.

637
00:37:47.517 --> 00:37:48.852
That's a lot of taxes.

638
00:37:48.935 --> 00:37:51.855
Well. Dad taught me.
real estate's king.

639
00:37:53.356 --> 00:37:54.774
You liked your dad a lot. huh?

640
00:37:56.067 --> 00:37:57.736
I did.

641
00:37:57.819 --> 00:37:59.488
I mean. he was a hard man.

642
00:37:59.571 --> 00:38:00.989
Hard to please.

643
00:38:01.072 --> 00:38:03.825
Had a tough time keeping
his belt looped.

644
00:38:03.908 --> 00:38:08.497
but... you know.
dads get a bad rap. you know?

645
00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:10.207
They're getting us ready
for the real world.

646
00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:11.667
Uh-hmm.

647
00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:15.587
They're hard.
'cause the real world is hard.

648
00:41:04.714 --> 00:41:07.426
You can't be doin' that.

649
00:41:07.509 --> 00:41:10.428
Mrs. Piest.
please do not go there again.

650
00:41:13.264 --> 00:41:14.766
We understand.

651
00:41:18.103 --> 00:41:19.479
She understands.

652
00:41:21.773 --> 00:41:23.608
But he's a suspect. correct?

653
00:41:26.528 --> 00:41:29.155
There's only so much
I'm allowed to share with you.

654
00:41:31.616 --> 00:41:34.828
What I can say is that
we have been following him.

655
00:41:34.911 --> 00:41:36.621
Did you bring him in?

656
00:41:37.956 --> 00:41:39.625
Yes.

657
00:41:39.708 --> 00:41:42.585
But we don't have anything
to hold him on.

658
00:41:44.504 --> 00:41:46.631
How long
have you been following him?

659
00:41:47.632 --> 00:41:48.717
Last seven days.

660
00:41:51.219 --> 00:41:52.804
And you haven't arrested him?

661
00:41:52.887 --> 00:41:55.682
What. what if... seven days?

662
00:41:55.765 --> 00:41:57.100
What if he knows where Rob is?

663
00:41:59.060 --> 00:42:00.895
We have to get this right.

664
00:42:02.147 --> 00:42:04.691
It is imperative
that we get this right.

665
00:42:04.774 --> 00:42:07.110
My son is out there.

666
00:42:07.193 --> 00:42:08.487
I understand this. Mrs. Piest.

667
00:42:08.570 --> 00:42:09.571
-Elizabeth. please.
-No. don't say that.

668
00:42:09.654 --> 00:42:11.156
You don't. You don't understand.

669
00:42:11.239 --> 00:42:13.784
He's out there. He needs us.
-Stop it.

670
00:42:13.867 --> 00:42:15.911
We've been patient.
You disappeared.

671
00:42:15.994 --> 00:42:17.913
You didn't. didn't call us.
Didn't come by.

672
00:42:17.996 --> 00:42:20.874
Only now when I do something.
now you come?

673
00:42:20.957 --> 00:42:23.085
I want some goddamn answers!

674
00:42:23.168 --> 00:42:25.045
Okay.

675
00:42:26.963 --> 00:42:27.963
I'm sorry.

676
00:42:29.591 --> 00:42:31.551
You have nothing
to be sorry for.

677
00:42:34.179 --> 00:42:35.931
We just need time.

678
00:42:36.014 --> 00:42:40.811
I am asking you for more time.

679
00:42:40.894 --> 00:42:44.564
And I promise you.
I will be in touch.

680
00:42:46.316 --> 00:42:51.112
Rob's scared and alone.

681
00:43:05.168 --> 00:43:08.130
You guys wanna buy some weed?

682
00:43:10.048 --> 00:43:12.217
We know you got some in there.

683
00:43:12.300 --> 00:43:14.177
How 'bout some fried fish?

684
00:43:14.260 --> 00:43:15.679
Couple of beers?

685
00:43:16.888 --> 00:43:19.182
Come on. Come on in. Warm up.

686
00:43:20.308 --> 00:43:22.227
It's insultin' if you say no.

687
00:43:28.858 --> 00:43:30.193
I know it doesn't look possible.

688
00:43:30.276 --> 00:43:32.821
but you can fit
400 people in my yard.

689
00:43:32.904 --> 00:43:34.239
It's a code violation.

690
00:43:34.322 --> 00:43:36.325
Oh. listen to him.

691
00:43:36.408 --> 00:43:38.076
Don't go callin'
the fire marshal on me

692
00:43:38.159 --> 00:43:39.828
next year. okay?

693
00:43:39.911 --> 00:43:41.330
But it's always theme parties.
right?

694
00:43:41.413 --> 00:43:43.874
Um. we did Hawaii once.

695
00:43:43.957 --> 00:43:45.083
And a couple years back.

696
00:43:45.166 --> 00:43:47.169
there was a real
doozy bicentennial.

697
00:43:47.252 --> 00:43:50.005
Um. okay.
You got to check this out.

698
00:43:50.088 --> 00:43:51.840
Watch this. Huh?

699
00:43:53.049 --> 00:43:54.259
Is it the right way?

700
00:43:56.845 --> 00:43:58.555
Huh? Huh? Det. Fanholm: Hey.

701
00:43:58.638 --> 00:43:59.848
-What do you think?
-Yeah.

702
00:43:59.931 --> 00:44:03.685
Paul Revere's
got nothin' on me. right?

703
00:44:03.768 --> 00:44:05.020
The British are coming!

704
00:44:08.023 --> 00:44:09.942
Yeah. you should have seen
the whole thing though.

705
00:44:10.025 --> 00:44:10.943
It was really something.

706
00:44:11.026 --> 00:44:13.028
The wig. the white wig.
you know?

707
00:44:13.111 --> 00:44:14.154
-Right.
-And the lace

708
00:44:14.237 --> 00:44:16.573
and the long coat.

709
00:44:16.656 --> 00:44:18.742
Hey. do you guys know
Mrs. Rosalynn Carter?

710
00:44:18.825 --> 00:44:21.370
Oh. yeah. sure. John.
I know the First Lady.

711
00:44:21.453 --> 00:44:23.705
Oh. really? From where?

712
00:44:23.788 --> 00:44:25.582
Uh. just the news and whatever.

713
00:44:25.665 --> 00:44:27.793
Oh. Okay.

714
00:44:27.876 --> 00:44:30.254
That makes sense.
Yeah. No. I met her.

715
00:44:30.337 --> 00:44:31.755
I wouldn't even say that.

716
00:44:31.838 --> 00:44:34.341
I welcomed her personally.

717
00:44:34.424 --> 00:44:35.801
I threw an event for her.

718
00:44:35.884 --> 00:44:37.719
No. yeah.
Yeah. I got a photo of us.

719
00:44:37.802 --> 00:44:40.180
Right there.
Look. look. on the fridge.

720
00:44:40.263 --> 00:44:41.306
Place of honor.

721
00:44:41.389 --> 00:44:42.975
-Oh. yeah.
-Yeah.

722
00:44:43.058 --> 00:44:45.102
Would you guys check out my art
when you were in here?

723
00:44:45.185 --> 00:44:46.979
You like it?
Pretty damn good. huh?

724
00:44:47.062 --> 00:44:48.689
What do you think of my clowns?

725
00:44:48.772 --> 00:44:50.649
-I think there's a lot of them.
-A lot. yeah.

726
00:44:50.732 --> 00:44:52.025
Yeah. Well. yeah.

727
00:44:52.108 --> 00:44:55.070
I got an infinity for 'em
'cause I clown.

728
00:44:55.153 --> 00:44:57.072
What fuck does that mean?

729
00:44:57.155 --> 00:44:58.239
Well.

730
00:45:03.912 --> 00:45:06.665
Badoop. Badoop. Badoop.
Badoop. Badoop.

731
00:45:06.748 --> 00:45:09.126
Badoop. Badoop. Badoop. Badoop.

732
00:45:09.209 --> 00:45:12.087
Woo. Woo.

733
00:45:12.170 --> 00:45:15.215
Bloop. bloop. bloop. bloop.

734
00:45:16.841 --> 00:45:18.802
Pogo the Clown at your service.

735
00:45:18.885 --> 00:45:21.430
Desperate to meet ya.
-Get the fuck out of here.

736
00:45:21.513 --> 00:45:23.098
Okay. Okay.

737
00:45:23.181 --> 00:45:25.017
I created it myself.

738
00:45:25.100 --> 00:45:26.435
On account of me being Polish

739
00:45:26.518 --> 00:45:28.687
and on the go all the time.
"Po-go."

740
00:45:28.770 --> 00:45:30.105
-Yeah. yeah.
-Yeah. Do parades.

741
00:45:30.188 --> 00:45:33.066
10. 15 parades. charities.

742
00:45:33.149 --> 00:45:36.278
Oh. I did a cat show once
for the veep of Bressler.

743
00:45:36.361 --> 00:45:38.155
The ice cream company.
you know. 33 flavors?

744
00:45:38.238 --> 00:45:40.782
-Yeah.
-Yeah. yeah.

745
00:45:40.865 --> 00:45:43.327
Yeah. Yeah.
I enjoy it. clownin'.

746
00:45:43.410 --> 00:45:46.371
I mean. there's no money in it
but I find it relaxin'.

747
00:45:46.454 --> 00:45:50.250
You know. I can just regress
into bein' a kid.

748
00:45:50.333 --> 00:45:52.711
And there are things
that you can do

749
00:45:52.794 --> 00:45:54.755
that you wouldn't do
as a person. you know?

750
00:45:54.838 --> 00:45:56.798
You can sit on women's laps

751
00:45:56.881 --> 00:46:00.302
and. you know. honk. honk.
cop a feel.

752
00:46:00.385 --> 00:46:01.386
Okay.

753
00:46:01.469 --> 00:46:03.180
Yeah.

754
00:46:03.263 --> 00:46:06.308
They can't say anything
'cause you're a clown.

755
00:46:06.391 --> 00:46:09.770
You're a clown.

756
00:46:09.853 --> 00:46:11.730
I do crippled kids. sick kids.

757
00:46:11.813 --> 00:46:13.815
Oh. the look on their face.
-Yeah.

758
00:46:13.898 --> 00:46:17.235
It's like retarded
Christmas mornin'. you know.

759
00:46:17.318 --> 00:46:20.822
Oh. Yeah. it's the best.

760
00:46:20.905 --> 00:46:24.159
But. uh.
only if I'm in a good mood

761
00:46:24.242 --> 00:46:28.080
'cause if I'm in a bad mood.
it is bad for me to be a clown.

762
00:46:28.163 --> 00:46:30.290
Woo. I'm serious.

763
00:46:30.373 --> 00:46:32.834
'Cause some of those kids

764
00:46:32.917 --> 00:46:35.254
can just be little bastards.
you know?

765
00:46:35.337 --> 00:46:36.505
You know?
-Yeah.

766
00:46:36.588 --> 00:46:38.006
And instead of pinchin' them
on the cheek.

767
00:46:38.089 --> 00:46:39.841
you just want to whack
the shit out of them. right?

768
00:46:39.924 --> 00:46:41.760
-Yeah.
-feel that.

769
00:46:43.136 --> 00:46:45.055
But when you clown.

770
00:46:45.138 --> 00:46:48.141
you can hide who you really are

771
00:46:48.224 --> 00:46:49.810
and what you really feel.

772
00:46:49.893 --> 00:46:51.853
You just hide
behind a mask of love.

773
00:46:51.936 --> 00:46:53.313
and. happiness. and joy.

774
00:46:53.396 --> 00:46:54.439
But...

775
00:46:56.024 --> 00:46:59.820
I. I figure that clowns
can get away with anythin'.

776
00:46:59.903 --> 00:47:01.446
'Cause nobody would expect it.

777
00:47:03.114 --> 00:47:04.533
Shit.

778
00:47:04.616 --> 00:47:07.285
They could murder somebody
and get away with it...

779
00:47:09.913 --> 00:47:12.249
'cause nobody suspects a clown.

780
00:47:26.137 --> 00:47:27.430
Use your washroom.

781
00:48:12.684 --> 00:48:15.562
Oh. it sucks

782
00:48:17.522 --> 00:48:19.190
Yeah. We. we gotta go.

783
00:48:21.693 --> 00:48:22.944
What?

784
00:48:24.154 --> 00:48:25.905
Why're you leavin' so soon?

785
00:48:27.490 --> 00:48:29.242
Thanks for dinner. John.

786
00:48:47.552 --> 00:48:48.928
Answer it.

787
00:48:53.558 --> 00:48:55.977
Hello. Tovar residence.

788
00:48:57.228 --> 00:48:58.938
Dad. it's Mr. Fanholm.

789
00:49:00.065 --> 00:49:01.274
Give it here.

790
00:49:05.945 --> 00:49:07.114
Al.

791
00:49:07.197 --> 00:49:08.156
He finally did

792
00:49:08.239 --> 00:49:09.324
something fuckin' stupid.

793
00:49:09.407 --> 00:49:11.118
Huh? Wait. wait. wait.
Hang. hang on.

794
00:49:11.201 --> 00:49:12.410
Turn that thing off right now.

795
00:49:13.703 --> 00:49:14.997
Say again?

796
00:49:15.080 --> 00:49:16.164
Can you hear me?

797
00:49:16.247 --> 00:49:17.499
Yeah. yeah. Go ahead.

798
00:49:17.582 --> 00:49:19.167
He invited us in.

799
00:49:19.250 --> 00:49:22.212
out of the blue.
for food. beer. you know?

800
00:49:22.295 --> 00:49:24.006
There's something wrong
in there.

801
00:49:24.089 --> 00:49:25.382
There's a smell.

802
00:49:25.465 --> 00:49:27.050
What're you talkin' about?

803
00:49:27.133 --> 00:49:28.427
Been
around enough car accidents.

804
00:49:28.510 --> 00:49:30.970
crime scenes. morgues.

805
00:49:32.180 --> 00:49:35.016
There's a body
in that fuckin' house.

806
00:49:49.489 --> 00:49:51.325
Sam.

807
00:49:51.408 --> 00:49:53.535
Oh. shit. Are you headin' out?

808
00:49:53.618 --> 00:49:55.412
I don't wanna keep you.
-Hey. John.

809
00:49:55.495 --> 00:49:57.414
Uh. yeah. no.
thanks for stopping by.

810
00:49:57.497 --> 00:49:59.124
I. uh. meant to call you.
My fault.

811
00:49:59.207 --> 00:50:00.417
Yeah. No problem.

812
00:50:00.500 --> 00:50:02.002
I brought this for your boy.

813
00:50:02.085 --> 00:50:03.629
That's very kind of you. John.
Thanks.

814
00:50:03.712 --> 00:50:07.215
Well. you know.
it's a real pisser being sick.

815
00:50:07.298 --> 00:50:11.178
Yeah. Actually.
uh. Sammy. my son.

816
00:50:11.261 --> 00:50:12.596
he's. he's in the hospital now.

817
00:50:12.679 --> 00:50:14.181
-What?
-Yeah.

818
00:50:14.264 --> 00:50:15.307
Fever spiked.

819
00:50:15.390 --> 00:50:16.516
And. uh. Mary's over there now.

820
00:50:16.599 --> 00:50:18.101
And our baby's with my mom.

821
00:50:18.184 --> 00:50:19.269
And...
-Oh.

822
00:50:19.352 --> 00:50:21.480
...I'm headed
to the hospital now. so...

823
00:50:21.563 --> 00:50:23.148
Oh. shit.

824
00:50:23.231 --> 00:50:24.483
-But. um...
-I'm so sorry.

825
00:50:24.566 --> 00:50:26.193
Yeah. thank you. Thanks.

826
00:50:26.276 --> 00:50:27.569
But. uh. it's. it's why

827
00:50:27.652 --> 00:50:29.321
I. I didn't call you back. So...

828
00:50:29.404 --> 00:50:30.781
Uh-huh.

829
00:50:30.864 --> 00:50:33.158
...uh. if you can find time
tomorrow to come back in.

830
00:50:33.241 --> 00:50:35.243
I'll have the paperwork ready
for you to sign. okay?

831
00:50:35.326 --> 00:50:36.369
What for?

832
00:50:38.663 --> 00:50:40.540
The cease-and-desist letter.
John.

833
00:50:40.623 --> 00:50:42.709
-Oh.
-Against the Des Plaines PD.

834
00:50:42.792 --> 00:50:45.254
-Right.
-Get them off your back.

835
00:50:45.337 --> 00:50:47.756
Yeah. I. I think
you got a real case. so...

836
00:50:48.840 --> 00:50:51.218
Yeah. Yeah.

837
00:50:51.301 --> 00:50:52.511
That's. that's good. Sam.

838
00:50:52.594 --> 00:50:54.304
Thanks. That sounds real good.

839
00:50:54.387 --> 00:50:56.306
I'll come by tomorrow
and I'll sign everything.

840
00:50:56.389 --> 00:50:57.724
But. um. you got just a minute?

841
00:50:59.559 --> 00:51:03.647
John. I. I just told you.
my son's in the hospital. okay?

842
00:51:03.730 --> 00:51:05.440
-Yeah. I heard you.
-Well...

843
00:51:06.316 --> 00:51:08.568
But I've been contemplatin'.
okay?

844
00:51:09.569 --> 00:51:11.738
Um. just been thinkin'.

845
00:51:13.239 --> 00:51:15.700
This. this might influence
our case. Sam.

846
00:51:20.246 --> 00:51:22.416
I think I know
why they're following me.

847
00:51:25.418 --> 00:51:26.586
Okay.

848
00:51:28.755 --> 00:51:30.090
Okay. John.

849
00:51:40.642 --> 00:51:42.603
They think I did somethin'
with that Rob kid

850
00:51:42.686 --> 00:51:45.522
because I think they figured out

851
00:51:45.605 --> 00:51:47.733
that I brought him back
to my place.

852
00:51:51.403 --> 00:51:53.446
I thought you said
you didn't know him.

853
00:51:54.781 --> 00:51:57.367
Yeah. I did say that.
but. I mean...

854
00:51:58.743 --> 00:52:00.328
I. I met him...

855
00:52:01.204 --> 00:52:03.248
and I brought him
back to my place.

856
00:52:06.918 --> 00:52:10.422
And with you
bein' my lawyer and all now.

857
00:52:11.965 --> 00:52:13.758
I just wanna clear the air.

858
00:52:41.745 --> 00:52:42.871
Good mornin'.

859
00:52:42.954 --> 00:52:44.748
Allen. Mike.

860
00:52:44.831 --> 00:52:45.749
Is everything okay?

861
00:52:45.832 --> 00:52:47.208
He's been here all night.

862
00:52:51.671 --> 00:52:53.423
You guys gonna be here a while?

863
00:52:53.506 --> 00:52:55.425
-We go where he goes.
-Hey. look. Sam.

864
00:52:55.508 --> 00:52:56.760
We're just trying
to be stand up here.

865
00:52:56.843 --> 00:52:58.053
We got another warrant.

866
00:52:58.136 --> 00:52:59.936
We're gonna hit his house
in a bit. all right?

867
00:53:04.267 --> 00:53:05.435
Listen...

868
00:53:06.853 --> 00:53:08.438
if he tries to leave...

869
00:53:09.856 --> 00:53:11.941
shoot out his fucking tires.

870
00:53:13.860 --> 00:53:15.528
What the hell
are you talking about?

871
00:53:17.447 --> 00:53:18.698
What happened in there?

872
00:53:23.536 --> 00:53:25.872
I can't. I gotta go back...

873
00:53:27.749 --> 00:53:30.794
get back to the office
before anybody goes back.

874
00:53:43.556 --> 00:53:44.974
Fuck.

875
00:55:13.813 --> 00:55:15.315
Whoa.

876
00:55:30.705 --> 00:55:32.040
Get me Kozenczak.

877
00:56:22.424 --> 00:56:23.550
Ugh.

878
00:56:28.763 --> 00:56:29.763
Shit.

879
00:56:36.730 --> 00:56:38.732
Yeah. the guy's out of control.
What do you want us to do?

880
00:56:42.110 --> 00:56:43.487
Take him.

881
00:56:43.570 --> 00:56:44.654
Okay.

882
00:57:11.014 --> 00:57:13.684
Somebody get me
a fucking shovel!

